# Design Rules - AgriAI Platform (Web & Mobile)

## ✨ Visual Language

* Use soft neutral backgrounds (e.g. #F8F9FA or #EDF1F5).
* Rounded corners: 12px for cards, 8px for buttons/inputs.
* Shadows should be subtle (e.g. Tailwind `shadow-sm`).
* Icons should be outlined and consistent across platforms (e.g. Heroicons, Lucide).
* Emphasize simplicity and clarity over density.
* **Primary color:** Use blue (`#2D9CDB`) across all components for consistency (replaces original green accent).

---

## 📱 Mobile-First Adjustments

* Prioritize full-width layout for readability.
* Hide secondary text blocks or group them under toggles when needed.
* The tab bar should always be visible at the bottom (Home, Analysis, Chat, Profile).
* Video/image previews must be tappable and scrollable.
* Ensure touch targets are ≥ 48x48px.

---

## 💬 Chat Interface

* Always visible or easily accessible (dock right on desktop, full screen on mobile).
* Avatars: Assistant left-aligned, User right-aligned.
* Consistent color scheme:

  * Assistant: light gray background (`#F1F3F5`)
  * User: brand-accented (e.g. `#2D9CDB`)
* Maintain message spacing: 8px between messages, 16px between user/assistant blocks.
* Use typing indicator or “Analyzing...” message for async states.

---

## 🌱 Crop Analysis Card

* Title: `Diagnóstico` (web and mobile), bold, 18px.
* Image or video always first; full width with play icon if video.
* Summary in paragraph format with 1-line preview on mobile.
* Include “Ask in chat” button on both views, styled with icon and label.

---

## 🌤️ Weather & Location Components

* Always show:

  * Location: coordinates or field label
  * Weather: temperature, humidity, icon
  * Alert badge if available: ⚠️ Heatwave / Storm, etc.
* Use icons inline on mobile, as cards in web.
* Alert message formatting: icon + short description, bolded key words.

---

## 📈 Graphs and Data (Web Only)

* Line charts must have smoothed curves (SPLINE) and labels by week.
* Cards must include:

  * Metric title (`Estimated Yield`)
  * Value with unit (`1200 tons`)
  * Change indicator (e.g. +10% in green, -5% in red).

---

## 🔤 Typography

* Font: `Inter` or `Public Sans`, 400/500/700 weights.
* Headings:

  * Mobile: 18–20px
  * Desktop: 24–32px
* Body: 14–16px, with 1.4–1.6 line height.

---

## 🧠 UX Consistency

* Every image must include a “summary + action” pair.
* Every analysis must link back to the chat (via question or suggested button).
* Error and alert states must be communicated visually and textually.

---

## 🧪 Accessibility

* Ensure minimum color contrast of 4.5:1.
* Use alt text on all crop images.
* All icons must include accessible labels (`aria-label`).

